### Describe Zod Schema with .describe() or .meta() (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs/content/metadata.mdx

Demonstrates how to attach a description to a Zod schema using the `.describe()` method (for Zod 3 compatibility) or the recommended `.meta()` method. This allows for associating custom metadata like descriptions with schema definitions.

```ts
const emailSchema = z.email();
emailSchema.describe("An email address");

// equivalent to
emailSchema.meta({ description: "An email address" });
```

--------------------------------

### Define Inline Metadata for Zod Object Properties (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs/content/metadata.mdx

Demonstrates the use of the `.register()` method to define metadata inline for individual properties within a Zod object schema. This allows associating specific descriptions or other metadata directly with schema fields during their definition.

```ts
const mySchema = z.object({
  name: z.string().register(myRegistry, { description: "The user's name" }),
  age: z.number().register(myRegistry, { description: "The user's age" })
})
```

--------------------------------

### Add Description to Zod Schema with `describe`

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs-v3/README.md

Shows how to add a `description` property to a Zod schema using the `.describe()` method. This is useful for documenting the purpose of a field, especially when integrating with schema generation tools like `zod-to-json-schema`.

```ts
const documentedString = z
  .string()
  .describe("A useful bit of text, if you know what to do with it.");
documentedString.description; // A useful bit of text…
```

--------------------------------

### Registering Zod Schema Metadata for JSON Schema

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs/content/json-schema.mdx

This snippet shows two ways to attach metadata to a Zod schema using `meta()` (for standard Zod) and `register()` (for Zod Mini). The attached metadata, such as `title` and `description`, is then included in the generated JSON Schema when `z.toJSONSchema` is called.

```ts
import * as z from "zod";

// `.meta()` is a convenience method for registering a schema in `z.globalRegistry`
const emailSchema = z.string().meta({ 
  title: "Email address",
  description: "Your email address"
});

z.toJSONSchema(emailSchema);
// => { type: "string", title: "Email address", description: "Your email address", ... }
```

```ts
import * as z from "zod";

// `.meta()` is a convenience method for registering a schema in `z.globalRegistry`
const emailSchema = z.string().register(z.globalRegistry, { 
  title: "Email address",
  description: "Your email address"
});

z.toJSONSchema(emailSchema);
// => { type: "string", title: "Email address", description: "Your email address", ... }
```

--------------------------------

### Add Metadata to Zod Schemas with .meta() (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs/content/v4/index.mdx

The `.meta()` method allows adding arbitrary metadata to a Zod schema. It is immutable, returning a new schema instance. This is the preferred method over `.describe()` for adding descriptive information, which can later be used for purposes like JSON Schema conversion.

```typescript
z.string().meta({
  id: "email_address",
  title: "Email address",
  description: "Provide your email",
  examples: ["naomie@example.com"]
});
```

```typescript
z.string().describe("An email address");

// equivalent to
z.string().meta({ description: "An email address" });
```

--------------------------------

### Add metadata to the global Zod registry

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs/content/v4/index.mdx

Illustrates how to use Zod's built-in `z.globalRegistry` to add common JSON Schema-compatible metadata to a schema. This global registry can store details like `id`, `title`, `description`, and `examples`, as well as custom properties for broad accessibility.

```ts
z.globalRegistry.add(z.string(), {
  id: "email_address",
  title: "Email address",
  description: "Provide your email",
  examples: ["naomie@example.com"],
  extraKey: "Additional properties are also allowed"
});
```

--------------------------------

### Register Metadata to Zod Global Registry (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs/content/metadata.mdx

Shows how to register metadata for a Zod schema, such as an email validator, in the `z.globalRegistry` using the `.register()` method. This example includes common metadata fields like `id`, `title`, `description`, and custom fields like `examples`.

```ts
import * as z from "zod";

const emailSchema = z.email().register(z.globalRegistry, { 
  id: "email_address",
  title: "Email address",
  description: "Your email address",
  examples: ["first.last@example.com"]
});
```

--------------------------------

### Retrieve Metadata from Schema with .meta() (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs/content/metadata.mdx

Illustrates how to retrieve the metadata associated with a specific Zod schema instance by calling the `.meta()` method without any arguments. This allows access to previously registered metadata.

```ts
emailSchema.meta();
// => { id: "email_address", title: "Email address", ... }
```

--------------------------------

### Register Metadata to Global Registry with .meta() (Zod)

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs/content/metadata.mdx

Provides a convenient and concise way to register metadata for a schema directly into `z.globalRegistry` using the `.meta()` method. This is specific to the full Zod library and allows easy assignment of common metadata fields.

```ts
const emailSchema = z.email().meta({ 
  id: "email_address",
  title: "Email address",
  description: "Please enter a valid email address"
});
```

--------------------------------

### Create a Zod Registry with Typed Metadata (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs/content/metadata.mdx

Demonstrates how to initialize a Zod registry and specify the expected type for its associated metadata. This ensures type safety when attaching metadata to schemas within this registry.

```ts
import * as z from "zod";

const myRegistry = z.registry<{ description: string }>();
```

--------------------------------

### Understand Zod Schema Metadata Immutability (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs/content/metadata.mdx

Explains that metadata is tied to a specific schema instance in Zod. When schema methods return a new instance, like `refine()`, the new instance does not inherit metadata from the original, demonstrating Zod's immutability principle.

```ts
const A = z.string().meta({ description: "A cool string" });
A.meta(); // => { description: "A cool string" }

const B = A.refine(_ => true);
B.meta(); // => undefined
```

--------------------------------

### Enforce Metadata Type in Zod Registry (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs/content/metadata.mdx

Shows how TypeScript enforces the metadata type defined for a Zod registry. It demonstrates a successful assignment matching the type and a failed assignment where the value type does not conform to the registry's specified metadata type.

```ts
myRegistry.add(mySchema, { description: "A cool schema!" }); // ✅
myRegistry.add(mySchema, { description: 123 }); // ❌
```

--------------------------------

### Manage Schemas in a Zod Registry (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs/content/metadata.mdx

Illustrates the core operations for managing schemas within a Zod registry: adding a schema with metadata, checking its existence, retrieving its metadata, removing it, and clearing the entire registry. This provides a comprehensive overview of registry manipulation.

```ts
const mySchema = z.string();

myRegistry.add(mySchema, { description: "A cool schema!"});
myRegistry.has(mySchema); // => true
myRegistry.get(mySchema); // => { description: "A cool schema!" }
myRegistry.remove(mySchema);
myRegistry.clear(); // wipe registry
```

--------------------------------

### Conveniently register schema metadata using .register() method

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs/content/v4/index.mdx

Shows an alternative, more convenient way to add metadata to a schema registry using the `.register()` method directly on the schema. Unlike most Zod methods, `.register()` modifies the schema in place and returns the same schema instance, streamlining metadata assignment.

```ts
emailSchema.register(myRegistry, { title: "Email address", description: "..." })
// => returns emailSchema
```

--------------------------------

### Augment Zod GlobalMeta Interface for Custom Fields (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs/content/metadata.mdx

Demonstrates how to extend the `GlobalMeta` interface in Zod using TypeScript's declaration merging. This allows developers to add custom fields, like `examples`, to the global registry's metadata type, enhancing its flexibility.

```ts
declare module "zod" {
  interface GlobalMeta {
    // add new fields here
    examples?: unknown[];
  }
}

// forces TypeScript to consider the file a module
export {}
```

--------------------------------

### Create a Generic Zod Registry without Metadata Type (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs/content/metadata.mdx

Illustrates how to create a Zod registry without specifying a metadata type. In this configuration, the registry acts as a simple collection of schemas, without requiring any metadata to be associated with them.

```ts
const myRegistry = z.registry();

myRegistry.add(z.string());
myRegistry.add(z.number());
```

--------------------------------

### Add a schema and its metadata to a Zod registry

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs/content/v4/index.mdx

Demonstrates adding an existing Zod schema along with its associated metadata to a custom registry using the `myRegistry.add()` method. This approach allows for decoupling metadata from schema definitions, enabling easier retrieval via `myRegistry.get()`.

```ts
const emailSchema = z.string().email();

myRegistry.add(emailSchema, { title: "Email address", description: "..." });
myRegistry.get(emailSchema);
// => { title: "Email address", ... }
```

--------------------------------

### Reference Inferred Types in Zod Custom Registry (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs/content/metadata.mdx

Shows how to define a custom Zod registry where the metadata type references the inferred output type (`z.$output`) of the schema. This enables storing examples or other type-dependent data directly within the metadata for different schema types, enhancing type safety and utility.

```ts
import * as z from "zod";

type MyMeta = { examples: z.$output[] };
const myRegistry = z.registry<MyMeta>();

myRegistry.add(z.string(), { examples: ["hello", "world"] });
myRegistry.add(z.number(), { examples: [1, 2, 3] });
```

--------------------------------

### Including Custom Metadata in Zod JSON Schema

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs/content/json-schema.mdx

Demonstrates that any custom metadata fields added to a Zod schema using `.meta()` are directly copied into the resulting JSON Schema object. This allows for flexible extension of the generated schema with arbitrary properties.

```ts
const schema = z.string().meta({
  whatever: 1234
});

z.toJSONSchema(schema);
// => { type: "string", whatever: 1234 }
```

--------------------------------

### Create a Zod schema metadata registry

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs/content/v4/index.mdx

Illustrates how to initialize a custom schema registry using `z.registry()`. This registry allows associating strongly-typed metadata with Zod schemas, providing a flexible way to attach additional information without modifying the schema itself.

```ts
import * as z from "zod";

const myRegistry = z.registry<{ title: string; description: string }>();
```

--------------------------------

### Register Schema Using .register() Method (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs/content/metadata.mdx

Explains how to use the `.register()` method directly on a Zod schema to conveniently add it to a specified registry along with its metadata. This method returns the original schema instance, allowing for method chaining.

```ts
const mySchema = z.string();

mySchema.register(myRegistry, { description: "A cool schema!" });
// => mySchema
```
